node.text:
‚ÄúBlack Spine‚Äù If it weren‚Äôt for Procreate‚Äôs video recording and instagram‚Äôs story feature, I wouldn‚Äôt have ever started doing videos.
.
Now I just love the process of editing my painting videos. Sure it takes a lot of work.  I tore the footage recorded for ‚ÄúBlack Spine‚Äù to SHREDS as I pieced it together. There‚Äôs a 3 page script for it that I trashed because I realised that the music composed by Tristan Barton tells the story better than my words for this one.
.
The short clips in between were shot in Iceland and that landscape was the inspiration for the style of this scenery.
. 
The symbolism of dormant anxiety was something that came to me pretty early in the painting process and I would have felt disrespectful to the idea if I had gone with my pre-planned script for this.
.
Some videos seem like I‚Äôm making them 100% for myself and after seeing how many times I had seen it myself before I hit the publish button. Well it‚Äôs safe to say it was worth it :) #artwork

‚ÄúNight Owl Coffee Shop‚Äù I don‚Äôt usually give homework on my channel but since few people asked me advice on how to get into pixel art I created a 3 step process that‚Äôs outlined in my recent video tutorial. .
As a teacher I first started teaching process like everyone else but overtime it just felt too fake because I knew it didn‚Äôt reflect my day to day practice of making art.
.
Now my approach is more focused on creating art while practicing. It‚Äôs also easier to be encouraging this way because now I actually believe in what I‚Äôm saying and seeing results in student work has definitely made me see the difference.
.
Also check out @nmvnart ‚ÄòS latest pixel art piece. Awesome stuff! ü¶â ‚òïÔ∏è #artwork

node.text:
‚ÄúBleached by Moonlight‚Äù It‚Äôs my assumption that most artists think of thumbnails as something you only do as an art class assignment. It‚Äôs too bothersome and time consuming for everyday situations. I think those feelings come from simple misunderstanding of how thumbnails should be made. This is not the time nor the place to dump all your creative effort and work energy in this small step of the process. If you feel like crying on the bathroom floor after your thumbnails are done -stop it.
.
Every time I‚Äôve set thumbnails as an art assignment to the students; ALL of them have better thumbnails than I ever do. While this might boost their ego when showing their work to the class it‚Äôs preventing them from seeing what a powerful idea creation tool thumbnails can be when done right.
.
If you‚Äôve ever stared at a blank canvas frustrated that you have nothing to paint: I highly suggest giving thumbnails a try.
.
In my latest video I go through my own thumbnail process and set boundaries on time and detail so that this step of the process can be practical and useful when it‚Äôs needed. Link in bio.
#artwork
